    pearls: ["HFrEF = systolic failure (can't pump out); HFpEF = diastolic failure (can't fill properly) — both cause the same congestive symptoms but through different mechanisms", "S3 = HFrEF (rapid ventricular filling into dilated chamber); S4 = HFpEF (atrial contraction against stiff ventricle)", "SGLT2 inhibitors are the ONLY drug class with proven benefit in BOTH HFrEF AND HFpEF", "HFpEF is predominantly a disease of older women with HTN, obesity, DM, and AF — there are far fewer proven therapies compared to HFrEF", "The four pillars of HFrEF GDMT should be initiated concurrently when possible — each independently reduces mortality by 15-30%", "Cardiac MRI is the gold standard for EF measurement and can identify specific etiologies (scar pattern, infiltration, iron overload)"],
