        options: ["HFNC is less expensive", "HFNC meets the patient's peak inspiratory flow demand, preventing room air entrainment and delivering precise FiO₂", "HFNC eliminates the need for humidification", "HFNC can only be used in the ICU"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Standard nasal cannula delivers 1-6 L/min, which is far below the patient's peak inspiratory flow (30-120 L/min), resulting in room air entrainment that dilutes the delivered FiO₂. HFNC at 20-60 L/min meets or exceeds inspiratory demand, ensuring precise FiO₂ delivery."
